### Acceptance criteria notes

Acceptance criteria must be **verifiable** — not "the page should look good", but "contrast ≥ 4.5:1".

**Acceptance layering**: preserve upstream product AC IDs unchanged. Design-derived DAC IDs add verifiable design constraints; task specs may reference them but never renumber them.

Good AC examples:
- AC-F01-001: button text-to-background contrast ≥ 4.5:1 (WCAG AA)
- AC-F01-002: all interactive elements support keyboard Tab navigation
- AC-F01-003: mobile layout is single column, desktop is three columns

Bad AC examples (forbidden):
- "The page should look good" (not verifiable)
- "Good user experience" (not verifiable)

