## Success metrics (design completeness measure)

[After the design is done, what metrics measure design success? Meeting the bar means success]

- Metric 1: [e.g., all pages WCAG 2.1 AA compliant]
- Metric 2: [e.g., design system coverage 100%]
- Metric 3: [e.g., design spec deliverability check passed]

> Difference from "accessibility requirements": accessibility requirements are constraints that must be met (not meeting = defect), while success metrics are the measure of design completeness (meeting = success).

